"Educate first, refer second" builds trust rather than extracting value immediately. Smart positioning.
NSW focus allows depth that national competitors can't match.
Persona framework is genuinely useful — a first home buyer and an experienced investor need completely different guidance.
8-stage structure is comprehensive and memorable.
Well-timed — market volatility, rate uncertainty, and scheme changes create demand for guidance.
What's holding it back:

Competes with free — Revenue NSW, MoneySmart, REA, Domain, and dozens of mortgage brokers already publish guides. Your differentiation is thin without the partner network.
No moat — content can be copied. Calculators can be replicated. The only defensible asset is the professional network and brand trust.
Small TAM — NSW-only, English-only, web-only. Even with expansion plans, you're starting in a narrow lane.
